Title: Note on the point-splitting procedure to evaluate vacuum fluctuation in

certain cylindrically symmetric backgroundsAuthors: I. Brevik, G.E.A. Matsas and E.S. Moreira Jr

Comments: REVTeX file, 7 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D58 (1998) 027502

We revisit two-point function approaches used to study vacuum fluctuation inwedge-shaped regions and conical backgrounds. Appearance of divergent integralsis discussed and circumvented. The issue is considered in the context of amassless scalar field in cosmic string spacetime.